{
  "texts": [
    "Also, Liu et al. (2021) suggested a method for classifying AD by utilizing deep separable CNN.",
    "In place of traditional convolution, depthwise separable convolution (DSC) is employed.",
    "TL is additionally used to enhance model performance.",
    "GoogLeNet (Szegedy et al. 2015) and AlexNet (Krizhevsky et al. 2017), two trained models having average classification rates of 93.02% and 91.40%, respectively, are employed for TL, and DSC achieves an accuracy of 77.79%.",
    "The suggested neural network has a minimal power requirement, considerably reduced parameters, and computing costs."
  ]
}